Spring REST OpenAPI Tutorial

  This tutorial demonstrates that OfficeFloor REST endpoints declared as YAML files appear
  automatically in the OpenAPI specification generated by
  {{{https://springdoc.org}springdoc-openapi}}.  No additional configuration is needed — adding
  the springdoc dependency is sufficient.

  The tutorial exposes a simple product catalogue with two endpoints:

   * <<<GET /product>>> — returns a list of all products

   * <<<GET /product/\{id\}>>> — returns a single product by identifier

  {{{https://github.com/officefloor/OfficeFloor/tree/master/tutorials/springboot/SpringRestOpenApiHttpServer}Tutorial Source}}



*Maven dependency

  Add <<<springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui>>> alongside the OfficeFloor starter:

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/pom.xml|ignoreDownloadError=false}

  That is the only change required — OfficeFloor's built-in SpringDoc integration registers all
  YAML-declared endpoints with the <<<OpenApiCustomizer>>> at start-up.



*Application class

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestopenapi/SpringRestOpenApiApplication.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Response DTO with <<<@Schema>>> annotations

  Swagger annotations on the response class populate the component schema in the generated spec:

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestopenapi/Product.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Service beans

  A plain Spring <<<@Service>>> holds the in-memory catalogue:

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestopenapi/ProductCatalogueService.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*Service methods with <<<@Operation>>>

  <<<@Operation>>> on the service method populates the operation summary in the spec.
  The <<<ProductCatalogueService>>> is injected by type — no annotation needed on that parameter:

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestopenapi/ListProductsService.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/main/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestopenapi/GetProductService.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}



*YAML endpoint files

  Each endpoint is declared as a YAML file under <<<officefloor/rest/>>>:

+--
officefloor/rest/
├── product.GET.yml          →  GET /product
└── product/
    └── {id}.GET.yml         →  GET /product/{id}
+--

%{snippet|file=${basedir}/src/main/resources/officefloor/rest/product.GET.yml|ignoreDownloadError=false}

%{snippet|file=${project.build.directory}/site-snippets/product/id.GET.yml|ignoreDownloadError=false}


*Testing

  Tests verify both endpoint behaviour and that the paths appear in the live OpenAPI JSON at
  <<<GET /v3/api-docs>>>:

%{snippet|id=tutorial|file=${basedir}/src/test/java/net/officefloor/tutorial/springrestopenapi/SpringRestOpenApiTest.java|ignoreDownloadError=false}

  The Swagger UI is available at <<<http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html>>> when the application
  is running.



